main event: A ground radar and visual sighting of an unidentified object in Cunningham, Tennessee on October 15, 1956.
interesting points: The object remained stationary and was the size of a car's silhouette reflected on the ground.
The object moved and then went out when it stopped.
During the second sighting, the object moved on a straight line at an azimuth of 180 degrees and an elevation of 45 degrees, and was visible through binoculars for 20 minutes.
The witnesses stated that the object reappeared at 23:06Z and moved in the same direction as before.
The report indicates that this was the third sighting and the description suggests it may have been a balloon.
photographs: no, the report does not include any photographs
